  "prompt": "Account opening in Zerodha states 48 hours, I have submitted all documents and it has been 10 days with no luck. Pathetic support, how to escalate?",
  "response": "If you are facing delays with your account opening in Zerodha and have not received satisfactory support, here are some steps you can take to escalate your issue:\n\n1. **Check Email Notifications**: Ensure you haven\u2019t missed any communication from Zerodha in your email, including in your spam/junk folders.\n\n2. **Contact Customer Support**: Before escalating, it\u2019s a good idea to try reaching out to their customer support again. You can do this through:\n   - **Phone**: Call Zerodha\u2019s customer support number available on their website.\n   - **Email**: Send a detailed email to their support team at support@zerodha.com explaining your situation.\n   - **Web Support**: Use the support chat feature on their website if available.\n\n3. **Follow Up**: If you have already contacted support, make sure to follow up on your initial inquiry. Reference your previous correspondence and mention that it\u2019s been 10 days.\n\n4. **Use Social Media**: Companies often respond quickly to public inquiries. Use platforms like Twitter or Facebook to reach out to Zerodha, detailing your issue and tagging them for visibility.\n\n5. **Escalation to Higher Authority**: If there is no response, you can request your issue to be escalated during your communication with customer support.\n\n6. **Zerodha\u2019s Complaint Registration**: If the problem persists, you can register a formal complaint on the Zerodha support portal. Look for an option related to grievance redressal.\n\n7. **Investor Grievance Redressal System**: If all else fails, you can escalate your complaint to the relevant financial regulatory body in your country (for instance, SEBI in India) if you believe your issue has not been resolved satisfactorily.\n\n8. **Keep Records**: Document all your communications with Zerodha, including dates, times, and any reference numbers. This will be helpful if you need to escalate further.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to address your issue more effectively.",
